# 📋 Changelog

All notable changes to ISTIC-QualityHub are documented here.
Tous les changements notables d'ISTIC-QualityHub sont documentés ici.

Format based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).
Versioning follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

---

## [Unreleased]

### 🎫 Ticket Manager v1.0 *(in development)*
- Core ticket management (create, assign, track, close)
- Recurring tasks planner
- SLA compliance dashboard

---

## [2.0.0] — Risk Manager v2 — 2026

### Added
- ✅ Custom institution logo upload (stored as base64, persists in localStorage)
- ✅ Dynamic action checklist — sub-tasks with automatic progress calculation
- ✅ Periodic review alerts on dashboard (overdue = red, due soon = orange)
- ✅ Modification history / audit trail per risk and opportunity
- ✅ Stakeholder communication log per risk (ISO 31000 §5.4)
- ✅ Quality objectives linking — relate risks/opportunities to ISO 21001 §6.2 objectives
- ✅ Management review module (ISO 21001 §9.3) with PDF report
- ✅ Academic cycle filter (S1 / S2 / custom date range)
- ✅ KPI dashboard — C3 treatment rate, action completion rate, avg closure delay, linking rate
- ✅ Export Excel (XLSX) — 4 sheets: Risks / Opportunities / Action Plan / KPIs
- ✅ Export JSON — full data backup
- ✅ Import JSON — restore data, share between devices
- ✅ Auto-update action status based on checklist completion (100% → Réalisée)
- ✅ Header updated to show ISO 31000 / ISO 21001 compliance

### Changed
- Navigation header updated to include "Revue direction" tab
- Settings page redesigned with logo upload zone
- Action form: replaced manual progress slider with checklist system
- PDF export updated with ISO compliance mention in footer

### Fixed
- Template literal syntax error in `renderRevue()` — semicolon inside `${}` expression caused full JS crash
- `objectifs` array initialized correctly on first run

---

## [1.0.0] — Risk Manager v1 — 2026

### Added
- ✅ Risk register with V×G criticality matrix (C1/C2/C3)
- ✅ Opportunity register with Efforts×Advantage matrix (P1/P2/P3)
- ✅ Action plan with manual progress slider
- ✅ Process and actor management in Settings
- ✅ Interested parties register
- ✅ Dashboard with risk/opportunity distribution charts
- ✅ Effectiveness evaluation modal
- ✅ PDF export (jsPDF + AutoTable, landscape A4)
- ✅ Browser localStorage persistence
- ✅ Dashboard stats: total risks, C3 risks, opportunities, actions, completed actions

---

## Version Numbering / Numérotation des versions

```
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH

MAJOR — Breaking change or complete redesign of an app
MINOR — New feature added (backward compatible)
PATCH — Bug fix or small improvement

Examples:
  1.0.0 → First release
  1.1.0 → New feature added
  1.1.1 → Bug fix
  2.0.0 → Major redesign or new app added to suite
```

